<subSubSection id="C3466511FFCEFFF175D1AC42C4A2ACEA" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="520" pageId="13" pageNumber="519" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE3369AFFCEFFF275D1AC42C33EAB3D" blockId="13.[151,1437,1615,2038]" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCEFFF275D1AC42C730AA31" bold="true" box="[151,349,1615,1642]" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Diagnosis. Male.</emphasis>
Two pairs of ocellar setae; thorax yellow with scutum and scutellum brown to black (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFCEFFF27060AC42C3E2AA31" box="[1318,1423,1615,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[159,1437,312,1202]" captionTargetId="figure-52@14.[150,1437,308,1202]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus ciliaticosta Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. ♂ (A–E). A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view (black arrow indicating the membranous area); E. Phallus, posterior view. ♀ (F–G). F. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; G. Apex of abdomen, dorsal pieces in dorsal view, ventral pieces in ventral view. Scale bars, figures A = 1 mm; B, F, G = 0.3 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm.Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; epand, epandrium; gen fk, genital fork; gen ch, genital chamber; m ce, median cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; st, sternite; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921377/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
); hind tibia (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFCEFFF27451AC7EC7ECAAD5" box="[279,385,1651,1678]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[159,1437,312,1202]" captionTargetId="figure-52@14.[150,1437,308,1202]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus ciliaticosta Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. ♂ (A–E). A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view (black arrow indicating the membranous area); E. Phallus, posterior view. ♀ (F–G). F. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; G. Apex of abdomen, dorsal pieces in dorsal view, ventral pieces in ventral view. Scale bars, figures A = 1 mm; B, F, G = 0.3 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm.Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; epand, epandrium; gen fk, genital fork; gen ch, genital chamber; m ce, median cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; st, sternite; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921377/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
) with 5–6 dorsal setae; wing brown infuscated along costal cell and apex of cell r 
<subScript id="17D834DFFFCEFFF27005AC8BC331AACF" attach="left" box="[1347,1372,1670,1684]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">2+3</subScript>
(
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFCEFFF27029AC7EC6A6AAE9" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[159,1437,312,1202]" captionTargetId="figure-52@14.[150,1437,308,1202]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus ciliaticosta Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. ♂ (A–E). A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view (black arrow indicating the membranous area); E. Phallus, posterior view. ♀ (F–G). F. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; G. Apex of abdomen, dorsal pieces in dorsal view, ventral pieces in ventral view. Scale bars, figures A = 1 mm; B, F, G = 0.3 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm.Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; epand, epandrium; gen fk, genital fork; gen ch, genital chamber; m ce, median cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; st, sternite; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921377/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
); cell dm somewhat acute; veins M 
<subScript id="17D834DFFFCEFFF2771EACA7C40DAAE3" attach="left" box="[600,608,1706,1720]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">1</subScript>
, M 
<subScript id="17D834DFFFCEFFF277C1ACA7C4E2AAE3" attach="left" box="[647,655,1706,1720]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">2</subScript>
and CuA+CuP somewhat distinct; tergite 8 (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFCEFFF271C0AC9AC37DAAE9" box="[1158,1296,1687,1714]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[159,1437,312,1202]" captionTargetId="figure-52@14.[150,1437,308,1202]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus ciliaticosta Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. ♂ (A–E). A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view (black arrow indicating the membranous area); E. Phallus, posterior view. ♀ (F–G). F. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; G. Apex of abdomen, dorsal pieces in dorsal view, ventral pieces in ventral view. Scale bars, figures A = 1 mm; B, F, G = 0.3 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm.Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; epand, epandrium; gen fk, genital fork; gen ch, genital chamber; m ce, median cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; st, sternite; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921377/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Figs 10B, C</figureCitation>
) with somewhat acute truncated distal projection; epandrium (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFCEFFF27789ACB6C55EAA8D" box="[719,819,1723,1750]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[159,1437,312,1202]" captionTargetId="figure-52@14.[150,1437,308,1202]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus ciliaticosta Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. ♂ (A–E). A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view (black arrow indicating the membranous area); E. Phallus, posterior view. ♀ (F–G). F. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; G. Apex of abdomen, dorsal pieces in dorsal view, ventral pieces in ventral view. Scale bars, figures A = 1 mm; B, F, G = 0.3 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm.Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; epand, epandrium; gen fk, genital fork; gen ch, genital chamber; m ce, median cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; st, sternite; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921377/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
) with anterodorsal and posterodorsal lobes of subequal height; anterior cercus (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFCEFFF274E4ACD2C46BAAA1" box="[418,518,1759,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[159,1437,312,1202]" captionTargetId="figure-52@14.[150,1437,308,1202]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus ciliaticosta Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. ♂ (A–E). A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view (black arrow indicating the membranous area); E. Phallus, posterior view. ♀ (F–G). F. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; G. Apex of abdomen, dorsal pieces in dorsal view, ventral pieces in ventral view. Scale bars, figures A = 1 mm; B, F, G = 0.3 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm.Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; epand, epandrium; gen fk, genital fork; gen ch, genital chamber; m ce, median cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; st, sternite; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921377/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
) somewhat narrow; median cercus with slender setae; posterior cercus (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFCEFFF27076ACD2C3F9AAA1" box="[1328,1428,1759,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[159,1437,312,1202]" captionTargetId="figure-52@14.[150,1437,308,1202]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus ciliaticosta Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. ♂ (A–E). A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view (black arrow indicating the membranous area); E. Phallus, posterior view. ♀ (F–G). F. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; G. Apex of abdomen, dorsal pieces in dorsal view, ventral pieces in ventral view. Scale bars, figures A = 1 mm; B, F, G = 0.3 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm.Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; epand, epandrium; gen fk, genital fork; gen ch, genital chamber; m ce, median cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; st, sternite; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921377/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
) with apex acute and with a few long slender setae at margin, with wide ventral protuberance and many marginal yellow setae; hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFCEFFF27481AD2AC440AB19" box="[455,557,1831,1858]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[159,1437,312,1202]" captionTargetId="figure-52@14.[150,1437,308,1202]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus ciliaticosta Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. ♂ (A–E). A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view (black arrow indicating the membranous area); E. Phallus, posterior view. ♀ (F–G). F. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; G. Apex of abdomen, dorsal pieces in dorsal view, ventral pieces in ventral view. Scale bars, figures A = 1 mm; B, F, G = 0.3 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm.Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; epand, epandrium; gen fk, genital fork; gen ch, genital chamber; m ce, median cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; st, sternite; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921377/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
) with distinct bifid branch posteriorly, with many setae along posterior margin and distinct membranous area; in posterior view with apical lateral projections inwardly directed (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFCEFFF271A7AD46C32AAB3D" box="[1249,1351,1867,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[159,1437,312,1202]" captionTargetId="figure-52@14.[150,1437,308,1202]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus ciliaticosta Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. ♂ (A–E). A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view (black arrow indicating the membranous area); E. Phallus, posterior view. ♀ (F–G). F. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; G. Apex of abdomen, dorsal pieces in dorsal view, ventral pieces in ventral view. Scale bars, figures A = 1 mm; B, F, G = 0.3 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm.Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; epand, epandrium; gen fk, genital fork; gen ch, genital chamber; m ce, median cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; st, sternite; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921377/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Fig. 10E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE3369AFFCEFFF27581AD7DC3F8ABAE" blockId="13.[151,1437,1615,2038]" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCEFFF27581AD7DC748ABD1" bold="true" box="[199,293,1904,1930]" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Female.</emphasis>
Hind tibia with 4 long dorsal setae and short dorsal pinnate setae along distal half; hind tarsomere 1 with 1 slender dorsal seta; sternite 8 (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFCEFFF27702AD9EC4CAABF5" box="[580,679,1939,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[159,1437,312,1202]" captionTargetId="figure-52@14.[150,1437,308,1202]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus ciliaticosta Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. ♂ (A–E). A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view (black arrow indicating the membranous area); E. Phallus, posterior view. ♀ (F–G). F. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; G. Apex of abdomen, dorsal pieces in dorsal view, ventral pieces in ventral view. Scale bars, figures A = 1 mm; B, F, G = 0.3 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm.Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; epand, epandrium; gen fk, genital fork; gen ch, genital chamber; m ce, median cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; st, sternite; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921377/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Fig. 10F</figureCitation>
) with a subapical paired sclerotized protuberance, medially with a longitudinal somewhat membranous line, laterally with median third less sclerotized; genital fork (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFCEFFF271ABADBAC31EAB89" box="[1261,1395,1975,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[159,1437,312,1202]" captionTargetId="figure-52@14.[150,1437,308,1202]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus ciliaticosta Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. ♂ (A–E). A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view (black arrow indicating the membranous area); E. Phallus, posterior view. ♀ (F–G). F. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; G. Apex of abdomen, dorsal pieces in dorsal view, ventral pieces in ventral view. Scale bars, figures A = 1 mm; B, F, G = 0.3 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm.Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; epand, epandrium; gen fk, genital fork; gen ch, genital chamber; m ce, median cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; st, sternite; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921377/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="519">Figs 10F, G</figureCitation>
) Yshaped with rather strong lateral arms and a median short protuberance ventrally, with genital chamber membranous.
</paragraph>
